The global non-alcoholic steatohepatitis (NASH) management market is expected to see significant growth and evolution by the year 2028. NASH, a form of non-alcoholic fatty liver disease (NAFLD), is becoming increasingly prevalent worldwide due to factors like sedentary lifestyles and unhealthy diets. This has led to a surge in demand for effective management solutions to address this chronic condition. The market is segmented by drug type, diagnosis, and treatment. Under drug type, key categories include vitamin E supplements, insulin sensitizers, lipid-lowering agents, probiotics, and others. In terms of diagnosis, blood tests and imaging studies are prominent methods utilized, among others. When it comes to treatment, medications, therapeutics, surgery, and other approaches play a crucial role in managing NASH.

